

** Nowait

  <example>
    select ... for update nowait
  </example>

** Monitor  Locks

  <example>
    SQL> @?/rdbms/admin/utllockt.sql
  </example>

** Dictionary Tables

  - = DBA_LOCK_INTERNAL =
  - = DBA_LOCKS = 
  - = DBA_DML_LOCKS =
  - = DBA_DDL_LOCKS =
  - = DBA_BLOCKERS = - holding locks
  - = DBA_WAITERS =  - waiting for locks

** Session

  - http://www.jlcomp.demon.co.uk/faq/locked_rows.html
  - http://www.jlcomp.demon.co.uk/faq/row_locker.html

  - The column 'lockwait' in v$session is not null if the session is
    waiting for a lock.

  - With the lockwait sid you can look further into v$lock, v$tables,
    and v$sql.

